  <h3>Frozen Honeydew Margarita</h3>
  <div class="ingredients">
  <p class="recipe">Do you find yourself with a surplus of melon in November? Probably not. So file this away for another day.</p>
    <ul class="recipe">
      <li>1 honeydew melon (the green kind, dude)</li>
      <li>3/4 cup white tequila</li>
      <li>1/3 cup fresh lime juice</li>
      <li>sugar, to taste</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

    <ol class="recipe">
      <li>Slice open your melon and remove the seeds.</li>
      <li><strong>DO THIS PART 3 HOURS OR A WEEK BEFORE </strong>You are going to freeze the insides of the melon, but you need it to be in bite-sized pieces so you can throw them in the blender. So chop up or scoop out the insides and put them in a freezer bag or something.</li>
      <li>When you're ready to party, puree in batches frozen honeydew in a blender with all of the ingredients except the sugar.</li>
      <li>Taste, and blend in sugar if needed.</li>
    </ol>

