<h3>Alice’s Brownies</h3>
<p class="recipe">Alice is my great aunt on my dad’s side. I don’t remember her that well, but I do have fond memories of these brownies. My mom makes them and they’re gooey and delicious. If they aren’t, you’re doing something wrong.</p>

<ul class="recipe">
<li>1/2 cup sugar</li>
<li>2 T butter</li>
<li>2 T water</li>
<li>2 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips</li>
<li>2 eggs</li>
<li>1 t. vanilla</li>
<li>2/3 cup unsifted flour</li>
<li>1/4 t. baking soda</li>
<li>1/4 t. salt </li>
<li>1/4 cup nuts (optional)</li>
</ul>

<ol class="recipe">
<li>Preheat oven to 325 F. </li>
<li>On stove, melt butter, add sugar and water. Remove from heat. </li>
<li>Add 1 cup of chocolate chips and stir. </li>
<li>Add eggs, vanilla, the remaining chocolate chips and nuts.</li>
<li>Greased 8” sq. for 25-30 minutes.</li>
</ol>


